# /etc/fw_env.config - CV1835 (Antminer S19j Pro Cvitek control board)
#
# CV1835 stores the U-Boot environment in a dedicated raw eMMC region.
# This is NOT a Bitmain-style "/dev/nand_env" device — Cvitek U-Boot 2018
# reads/writes a 128 KiB env block at a fixed eMMC offset.
#
# CRITICAL — these values are the dev-kit RE'd defaults from
# DCENT_OS_DEVELOPMENT_KIT_FROMRE1/bms19j_pro_porting_plan.md §7 and
# multi_platform_master.md §9. They are NOT live-verified against a
# bench unit. The first time this firmware is booted on a real CV1835
# carrier, the operator MUST re-confirm the offset by reading mmcblk0boot1
# (or the partition U-Boot stamps as `mmc env` target) BEFORE running
# fw_setenv. Wrong offset = trashed bootloader.
#
# Format:
#   <device>  <offset>  <env_size>  <flash_sector_size>  [<num_sectors>]
#
# CV1835 default eMMC env layout (from dev-kit handoff):
#   - Primary env: /dev/mmcblk0boot1 @ offset 0x0     (128 KiB)
#   - Redundant env: /dev/mmcblk0boot1 @ offset 0x40000 (128 KiB)
#
# Some CV1835 builds put env in mmcblk0p4 (the "sig.bin / DTB" region).
# The dev-kit references the boot1 partition variant, which is the
# safer of the two (boot1 is hardware-write-protected against runtime
# accidents, and U-Boot uses the eMMC boot-partition env API).
#
/dev/mmcblk0boot1   0x00000000   0x20000   0x200
/dev/mmcblk0boot1   0x00040000   0x20000   0x200
